[size=4][b]BetterBots — Smarter Solo Play Bots for Darktide[/b][/size]

Vanilla Solo Play bots don't use their career abilities. Turns out Fatshark wired up the whole ability activation system — behavior-tree node, condition guard, action-input queue — and then gated it behind a hardcoded whitelist that only allows two abilities. BetterBots lifts that cap and fills in the missing metadata so the rest of the infrastructure does its job.

The result: bots throw grenades, pop stances, charge into revives, ping specials, carry tomes, and generally stop feeling like dead weight.

[b]Solo Play only.[/b] Darktide uses dedicated servers, so gameplay mods only work when you host locally through [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/176]Solo Play[/url]. This mod does [b]not[/b] affect public matchmaking.

[size=3][b]Why use this mod?[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Bots actually fire their career abilities instead of sitting on them all mission
[*]Bots throw grenades and blitzes (19 templates across all six classes)
[*]Bots pre-buff before reviving, ping elites, push poxbursters, and stop chasing specials two rooms away
[*]Ammo, healing, and pickup policies defer to human players instead of hogging resources
[*]Bot profiles give you class-diverse loadouts instead of four copy-pasted veterans
[/list]

[size=3][b]New in v1.1.0 — Release Soak Fixes[/b][/size]

This one is mostly hardening from live Solo Play testing. Less glamorous than v1.0.0, but important: the mod now spends a lot less time being clever in places where bots should just avoid ruining your run.

[list]
[*][b]Daemonhost avoidance hardened:[/b] bots now detect passive and waking daemonhosts more reliably, suppress ranged fire, grenades, blitzes, combat abilities, sprinting, and dash/charge launches near them, and steer away without blocking narrow stairs as aggressively
[*][b]Barrel and hazard movement safety:[/b] fused barrels now emit buffered bot AoE threats from the explosion node when vanilla's origin is misleading, and ledge checks no longer block ordinary stairs/downhill movement
[*][b]Pickup follow-through fixed:[/b] explicit smart-tag pickup orders now become real bot pickup state, stale pickup refs are cleared before vanilla update, and books/stims/ammo crates no longer get stuck behind stale orders
[*][b]Healing priority fixed:[/b] scarce medicae charges now prefer the ally that needs the heal most, while still preserving Martyrdom Zealot wound stacks
[*][b]Scenario harness expanded:[/b] added mixed horde and daemonhost scenarios for repeatable validation instead of waiting for mission RNG
[*][b]Regression checklist added:[/b] the repo now has a release-soak checklist for abilities, blitzes, melee specials, ADS/hipfire, pickups, hazards, and performance
[/list]

[size=3][b]What bots can use[/b][/size]

[b]Combat abilities[/b]
[list]
[*]Veteran: Executioner's Stance, Voice of Command, Infiltrate
[*]Zealot: Fury of the Faithful, Shroudfield, relic
[*]Psyker: Scrier's Gaze, Venting Shriek, Telekine Shield
[*]Ogryn: Point-Blank Barrage, Bull Rush, Loyal Protector
[*]Arbites: Castigator's Stance, Break the Line, Nuncio-Aquila
[*]Hive Scum: Desperado (Focus), Rampage, Stimm Supply field — implemented but untested (I don't own the DLC)
[/list]

[b]Grenades and blitzes[/b]
[list]
[*]Standard grenades: frag, krak, smoke, fire, shock, cluster, rock
[*]Zealot Throwing Knives
[*]Psyker Assail, Smite, Chain Lightning
[*]Arbites whistle and shock mine
[*]Hive Scum Blinder, Chem, Boom Bringer — implemented but untested (DLC again)
[/list]

[size=3][b]What bots do better now[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Fire abilities when a fight actually calls for them (18 per-template heuristics)
[*]Pop defensive abilities before reviving a downed ally
[*]Stagger team cooldowns instead of dumping everything in the same second
[*]Guard allies doing objectives and pickups
[*]Ping elites and specials so you can see them
[*]Push poxbursters at melee range instead of wasting ammo shooting them
[*]Stay engaged in fights longer without wandering off to heal at 99%
[*]Give barrels, ledges, and sleeping daemonhosts a wider berth
[*]Pick appropriate melee attacks into hordes vs armor
[*]Use several weapon specials on purpose instead of ignoring them: power swords, chain weapons, thunder hammers, force swords, combat axes/swords/knives, power mauls, Ogryn shovels/clubs/pickaxes/combat blades, rippergun bayonets, direct ranged bashes/pistol whips, and supported shotgun special shells
[*]Carry scriptures and tomes for the team
[*]Hand healing items and ammo to humans first
[*]Steer the Arbites Cyber-Mastiff onto higher-priority targets
[/list]

[size=3][b]Settings you can control[/b][/size]

Everything new is toggleable or tunable. A few highlights:

[list]
[*]Aggression preset: Testing / Aggressive / Balanced / Conservative
[*]Per-group ability toggles: stances, charges, shouts, stealth, deployables, grenades
[*]Sprint distance, chase range, player-tag response, melee horde bias, rippergun bayonet/direct ranged bash range, warp-weapon max peril
[*]Melee and ranged behavior toggles also cover supported weapon specials
[*]Smart blitz targeting
[*]Daemonhost avoidance and hazard movement safety
[*]Poxburster safety
[*]Ammo reserve thresholds for bots and humans
[*]Human-likeness timing and pressure profiles (manual or auto-by-difficulty)
[*]Healing deferral
[*]Grimoire pickup (default off)
[*]Bot profile class selection and weapon quality
[*]Debug level, JSONL event log, and [font=Courier New]/bb_perf[/font] diagnostics
[/list]

[size=3][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/19]Darktide Mod Loader[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/8]Darktide Mod Framework (DMF)[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/176]Solo Play[/url]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/183]Tertium 5[/url] or [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/725]Tertium 6[/url] for class-diverse bots based on player profiles
[/list]

[b]Note:[/b] Tertium 5 crashes on Arbites and Hive Scum archetypes. Switch to [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/warhammer40kdarktide/mods/725]Tertium 6[/url] if that hits you.

[size=3][b]Install[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Extract [font=Courier New]BetterBots.zip[/font] into your Darktide [font=Courier New]mods/[/font] folder
[*]Add [font=Courier New]BetterBots[/font] to [font=Courier New]mods/mod_load_order.txt[/font] below [font=Courier New]dmf[/font]
[*]Re-patch mods
[/list]

[size=3][b]Quick check[/b][/size]

Start a Solo Play mission and look for [font=Courier New]BetterBots loaded[/font] in chat.

[size=3][b]Known issues[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Mods get disabled after every Darktide patch — re-run the toggle/patch script to re-enable.
[*]Hive Scum abilities and blitzes are implemented but unvalidated in-game. I don't own the DLC, so I rely on reports.
[*]Item-based abilities (Zealot relic, Psyker Force Field, Arbites Cyber-Mastiff, Hive Scum Stimm Supply) use a wield/use/unwield sequence that can break after a Darktide patch until the path is updated.
[/list]

[size=3][b]What I want to fix next[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Voidblast p1 live release proof / repair if the charged-release override still misses
[*]Tier 3 revive cover (approach-phase architecture — the earlier enter-hook approach didn't survive engine state changes)
[*]Broad give-to-ally / wound-cure pocketable distribution beyond the current self-use and crate-deploy policy
[*]Remaining weapon special actions like shield specials, combat-sword parries, and hold/release ranged bashes
[*]Rig-verified Crusher weakspot routing to replace the current provisional rear-head proxy
[*]User-authored bot profiles and a utility-score architecture for target selection
[/list]

